This paper is about natural language generation (NLG) using neural networks, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of neural language models and sequence-to-sequence models, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with the challenges of working with a morphologically rich language, which could fall under the category of natural language processing (cs.NE) or computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper presents a new dataset, which could also be relevant to the category of computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CY) if the dataset includes visual information about restaurants.
